         <entryFree xml:id="k000285" type="architectural feature">
            <term xml:id="term-k000285-1" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt">pozilingchuang</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000285-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant">破子櫺窗</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000285-3" xml:lang="zh-Hans">破子棂窗</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000285-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin">pòzilíngchuāng</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000285-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">p`o-tzu-ling-ch`uang</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000285-6" xml:lang="en" type="literal_translation">split bar window (lit.)</term>
            <idno type="URI">https://architecturasinica.org/keyword/k000285</idno>
            <note type="Note">
               <p>under construction</p>
               <p xml:lan="en">Poziling chuang, literally “split-bar window,” is a kind of window installed between pillars and on top of yaochuan (waist bar or wall divider). This type of window 
                  derives its name from the triangular cross-section of the bars filling the window frame, which are made in pairs by sawing a square-sectioned timber diagonally. In this type of 
                  window the bars are fixed, thus it cannot be opened.</p>
               <p xml:lan="en">According to Yingzao fashi, the height of poziling chuang is between 4 and 8 chi, nearly 1.25 to 2.50 meters. The number of bars is determined by the rule that the 
                  distance between each bar must be  0.1 chi. The width and height of the bars can be changed according to the height of the window.(Li 2009, 6.4b-5a)</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant">安裝在柱間腰串以上的不可啟閉窗戶形式，因其窗櫺截面為三角形（方形一破為二）得名。依照《營造法式》的規定（李 2009，6.4b-5a），破子櫺窗高四尺至八尺，約1.25公尺至2.50公尺之間。以窗櫺間空隙以
                  一吋為定法確定窗櫺條數，窗櫺的寬度和高度則隨窗高而變化。</p>
            </note>
